{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 13, "line_start": 13, "page_hint": null, "section": "Corrosion Testing Loops With Molten Salt", "text": "Fermi Price $\\leq {2.62}{c}^{n}$"}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 74, "line_start": 74, "page_hint": null, "section": "CONTENTS", "text": "Operation and Maintenance of a Test Loop 17"}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 90, "line_start": 90, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "Automatic controls and equipment were developed to prevent solidification of the salt mixtures (m.p., 800 to $1100^{\\mathrm{O}}\\mathrm{F}$ ) in the event of a loss of power."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 90, "line_start": 90, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "Most test loops are fabricated of 0.5-in.-o.d., 0.045-in.-wall tubing, and they operate with a temperature differential of up to $200^{\\mathrm{O}}\\mathrm{F}$ , a maximum wall temperature in the range 1200 to $1500^{\\mathrm{O}}\\mathrm{F}$ , and a salt flow rate of up to 3 gpm."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 90, "line_start": 90, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "Twenty-five test loops have been operated for an accumulated operating time of 290,000 hr."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 94, "line_start": 94, "page_hint": null, "section": "Introduction", "text": "The compatibility of a particular salt mixture with a proposed container alloy is determined, in part, by tests with thermal-convection loops, $^{1}$ and the most promising combinations of salt mixtures and structural material are then studied in forced-circulation corrosion test loops."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 94, "line_start": 94, "page_hint": null, "section": "Introduction", "text": "These loops simulate all essential reactor operating conditions except radiation. $^{2}$ The test stands and loops have been standardized to permit ready replacement and to minimize fabrication costs and installation time."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 98, "line_start": 98, "page_hint": null, "section": "Introduction", "text": "zirconium, thorium, and uranium in various proportions that give melting temperatures generally falling in the 800 to $1100^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ range. $^{3}$ Viscosity and density vary with each mixture."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 98, "line_start": 98, "page_hint": null, "section": "Introduction", "text": "A typical salt mixture has a viscosity of 10 centipoise and a specific gravity of 2.4 at $1100^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ ."}
{"claim_type": "table-reference", "line_end": 106, "line_start": 106, "page_hint": null, "section": "Description of Test Loop and Auxiliary Equipment", "text": "For most tests, 0.5-in.-o.d., 0.045-in.-wall tubing has been found to be suitable."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 123, "line_start": 123, "page_hint": null, "section": "Description of Test Loop and Auxiliary Equipment", "text": "4, the desired flow rate is determined within the limitations of allowable pump speed."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 125, "line_start": 125, "page_hint": null, "section": "Description of Test Loop and Auxiliary Equipment", "text": "4 was calculated according to the electrical resistance of the heater section tubing, the flow rate, and the desired bulk fluid temperature difference."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 125, "line_start": 125, "page_hint": null, "section": "Description of Test Loop and Auxiliary Equipment", "text": "The power required of the transformer was $58.8\\mathrm{Kw}$ at 1250 amp and 47.2 volts."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 125, "line_start": 125, "page_hint": null, "section": "Description of Test Loop and Auxiliary Equipment", "text": "The two heater sections, 96 in. and 109 in. in length, are connected to the power supply transformer in parallel and carry 665 and 585 amp, respectively."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 125, "line_start": 125, "page_hint": null, "section": "Description of Test Loop and Auxiliary Equipment", "text": "The shorter first section (96 in.) has less resistance and imparts a higher heat flux where the bulk fluid temperature is the lowest."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 125, "line_start": 125, "page_hint": null, "section": "Description of Test Loop and Auxiliary Equipment", "text": "The $\\mathbf{I}^{2}\\mathbf{R}$ heating is applied only to straight sections of the tubing, during normal operation, to eliminate hot spots caused by poor flow distribution in the tubing bends."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 136, "line_start": 136, "page_hint": null, "section": "Unclassified Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65066", "text": "At test conditions, from 350 to 700 amp of 60-cycle alternating current flows in each heater section at a potential of 25 to 50 v."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 138, "line_start": 138, "page_hint": null, "section": "Unclassified Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65066", "text": "The power for the heater section is supplied by a 110-kva transformer having a low-voltage high-current secondary winding, with a saturable-core reactor on the primary side."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 142, "line_start": 142, "page_hint": null, "section": "Unclassified Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65066", "text": "The transformer is connected to the loop heater lugs by a 500,000-circular-mills cable through a 1600-amp breaker."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 142, "line_start": 142, "page_hint": null, "section": "Unclassified Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65066", "text": "During normal operation the connections of the heater section are such that the current flow is confined to the two heater sections (4 connections to the loop)."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 142, "line_start": 142, "page_hint": null, "section": "Unclassified Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65066", "text": "However, when it is necessary to preheat or provide emergency heating to the entire loop, the 1600-amp breaker shown in Fig."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 142, "line_start": 142, "page_hint": null, "section": "Unclassified Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65066", "text": "1 is tripped, leaving only two connections to the loop."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 144, "line_start": 144, "page_hint": null, "section": "Unclassified Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65066", "text": "Over 40 of these pumps have been fabricated of four different materials."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 144, "line_start": 144, "page_hint": null, "section": "Unclassified Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65066", "text": "An accumulated total of approximately 450,000 hr of operation in corrosion testing loops and other high-temperature pumping applications has demonstrated their reliability.[4,5] As shown in Fig."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 144, "line_start": 144, "page_hint": null, "section": "Unclassified Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65066", "text": "6, the pump has an overhung vertical shaft with an oil-lubricated face seal above the liquid"}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 149, "line_start": 149, "page_hint": null, "section": "Unclassified Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65066", "text": "A pump speed of approximately 3000 rpm is used for most long-term operation."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 151, "line_start": 151, "page_hint": null, "section": "Unclassified Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65066", "text": "The centrifugal pump is driven through double V-belts by a variable-speed magnetic clutch and a 5 hp motor."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 151, "line_start": 151, "page_hint": null, "section": "Unclassified Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65066", "text": "Relay SR-3 automatically changes over to the auxiliary supply if any perturbation of the normal control occurs."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 171, "line_start": 171, "page_hint": null, "section": "Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65062", "text": "The flow of molten salt from the pump is past the drain-tank connection, through the first heater section, through a long-radius 180-deg bend, through the second heater section, through a coiled cooler, and back to the pump."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 171, "line_start": 171, "page_hint": null, "section": "Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65062", "text": "A separate 10-kva saturable core reactor and transformer are connected to the cooler coil for use in preheating or during an emergency alarm condition."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 171, "line_start": 171, "page_hint": null, "section": "Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65062", "text": "The control is set at a predetermined rate of approximately 300 amp and 15 v, and the power is applied automatically when required."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 173, "line_start": 173, "page_hint": null, "section": "Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65062", "text": "Other auxiliary equipment required for the operation of the loop include a 3000 cfm blower, a cooling oil supply, and the necessary utilities, such as cooling air for the frozen-plug valve, inert gas, and cooling water."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 173, "line_start": 173, "page_hint": null, "section": "Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65062", "text": "3 mounted on a mobile dolly for ease of fabrication, inspection, and installation."}
{"claim_type": "reactor-physics", "line_end": 175, "line_start": 175, "page_hint": null, "section": "Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65062", "text": "All critical loop welding is done by the Heliarc process with inert cover gas and backup purge according to a strict welding specification.7 All welds are inspected visually, by dye penetrant, and by x-ray."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 175, "line_start": 175, "page_hint": null, "section": "Ornl-Lr-Dwg 65062", "text": "After the heaters and thermocouples are attached, the loop is covered with 3 in. of high-temperature insulation."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 179, "line_start": 179, "page_hint": null, "section": "Alarm and Automatic-Action Controls", "text": "The salt in the cooler coil will become solid in less than 1 min if the flow is stopped and no external heat is applied."}
{"claim_type": "figure-reference", "line_end": 181, "line_start": 181, "page_hint": null, "section": "Alarm and Automatic-Action Controls", "text": "9, i.e., any condition which will cause flow stoppage or adverse temperatures, will automatically place the loop in an isothermal or safe condition by performing the actions listed at the bottom of the figure."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 181, "line_start": 181, "page_hint": null, "section": "Alarm and Automatic-Action Controls", "text": "To cover the possibility of the failure of the main power transformer, the ceramic standby heaters are connected after 2 sec, and they will maintain isothermal conditions until the main source of power is restored."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 181, "line_start": 181, "page_hint": null, "section": "Alarm and Automatic-Action Controls", "text": "9 are shown schematically in Fig."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 181, "line_start": 181, "page_hint": null, "section": "Alarm and Automatic-Action Controls", "text": "The battery-powered relay R-8 is de-energized by relay R-4 to perform the four functions which place the loop on"}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 188, "line_start": 188, "page_hint": null, "section": "Alarm and Automatic-Action Controls", "text": "Should a failure occur of the normal building feeder, a transfer to an alternate feeder is made automatically within 2 sec."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 188, "line_start": 188, "page_hint": null, "section": "Alarm and Automatic-Action Controls", "text": "The time-delay relay TD-1 and relay R-3 of Fig."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 188, "line_start": 188, "page_hint": null, "section": "Alarm and Automatic-Action Controls", "text": "7 will hold in the battery-powered relay R-8, allowing the transfer to be made without disturbing the operation of the loops."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 188, "line_start": 188, "page_hint": null, "section": "Alarm and Automatic-Action Controls", "text": "Should the building electrical power be unavailable for a period longer than 2 sec, the emergency diesel generator, which started immediately, would begin assuming the load through a sequential timer."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 188, "line_start": 188, "page_hint": null, "section": "Alarm and Automatic-Action Controls", "text": "Loads would be picked up alternately between motor startup and heater load until the entire facility of 15 loops had power reapplied within 40 sec after the interruption."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 188, "line_start": 188, "page_hint": null, "section": "Alarm and Automatic-Action Controls", "text": "The 300-kw capacity of the diesel generator is sufficient to operate the loops isothermally until normal building electrical power is again available."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 194, "line_start": 194, "page_hint": null, "section": "Operation and Maintenance of a Test Loop", "text": "When all the electrical, thermocouple and control circuits are tested satisfactorily and the loop is leaktight, the entire loop is preheated to $1100^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ with the pump shaft rotating slowly and the cooling oil circulating."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 199, "line_start": 199, "page_hint": null, "section": "Operation and Maintenance of a Test Loop", "text": "The first load of salt is circulated for a minimum of 2 hr to clean the system and is then dumped into the drain tank and removed."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 205, "line_start": 205, "page_hint": null, "section": "Operation and Maintenance of a Test Loop", "text": "The tests under this program have been operated with maximum wall temperatures of 1200 to $1500^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ , a temperature difference between the maximum wall temperature and the minimum fluid temperature of $200^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ , and flow rates up to 3 gpm."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 205, "line_start": 205, "page_hint": null, "section": "Operation and Maintenance of a Test Loop", "text": "Previously tests were conducted with wall temperatures of $1500^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ and higher."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 216, "line_start": 216, "page_hint": null, "section": "Summary", "text": "Twenty-five loops have been fabricated with both INOR-8 and Inconel and have operated under this program for an accumulated total of over 290,000 hr."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 216, "line_start": 216, "page_hint": null, "section": "Summary", "text": "Twenty of the loops, thirteen of which were fabricated of INOR-8 and seven of Inconel, operated from one to two and a half years before being terminated and examined metallographically."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 220, "line_start": 220, "page_hint": null, "section": "Summary", "text": "Corrosion specimen weight loss and salt sample data from these loops indicated that the primary corrosion product is chromium and that an essentially constant value was achieved after approximately 5000 hr of operation.[11]"}
